summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2010 KEYSTONE PASSPORT RV. THE CONTACT STATED THAT WHEN DRIVING AT VARIOUS SPEEDS, THERE WAS EXCESS CABLING DRAGGING ON THE ROAD. THERE WAS AN UNKNOWN WARNING LIGHT ILLUMINATED AND THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE RV ITSELF BEGAN TO DRAG. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT INSPECTED BY A DEALER NOR REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS CONTACTED, BUT THE CONTACT HAD NOT RECEIVED A RESPONSE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS APPROXIMATELY 3,000. THE VIN WAS UNAVAILABLE.
